    "P ′ = {X ∩ S ′ | X ∈ P }.A generated subframe of F is a subframe F ′ of F such that S ′ is closed under ⊑ and R i from F:3. if x ∈ S ′ and y ⊑ x, then y ∈ S ′; if x ∈ S ′ and xR i y, then y ∈ S ′.A selective subframe of F is a subframe F ′ of F such that:4. if x ∈ S ′ and y ⊑ x, then there is a z ∈ S ′ such that z ⊑ y. ifx ∈ S ′, xR i y, and u ⊑ y, then there is a z ∈ S ′ such that z ≬ u and xR i z.",
    "◁Note the following facts about Definition 5.52.",
    "First, a subframe of F is not guaranteed to be a possibility frame.",
    "Second, every generated subframe of F is a selective subframe of F, but not vice versa, as shown in Figure 5.2.",
    "Third, if F is a world frame, so ⊑ is identity, then every selective subframe of F is a generated subframe of F.Figure 5.2: A possibility frame (left) and one of its selective subframes (right) that is not a generated subframe."
